NAME
       bal connector - Generate and maintain Ballerina connector assets with AI
       assistance.

SYNOPSIS
       bal connector -h | --help
       bal connector openapi -i <openapi-spec> [-o <output-dir>] [options...]
       bal connector sdk <command> <arguments...> [options...]

DESCRIPTION
       The `bal connector` command provides AI-assisted workflows for
       generating, sanitizing, validating, testing, documenting, and
       maintaining Ballerina connectors from OpenAPI specifications or Java
       SDKs.

       Use one of the available workflows to generate connector assets.
       Each workflow exposes its own commands and options.

WORKFLOWS
       openapi
            Generate and maintain Ballerina connectors from OpenAPI
            specifications. Runs a configurable pipeline covering
            sanitization, client generation, code repair, test and example
            generation, and documentation.

       sdk
            Generate and maintain Ballerina connectors from Java SDKs.
            Provides discrete commands for SDK analysis, specification and
            IR generation, connector code generation, code repair, test and
            example generation, and documentation.

ENVIRONMENT
       ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
            Required for all workflow stages. Both the openapi and sdk
            workflows call the Anthropic API at every stage and will fail
            at startup if this variable is not set.

            Set the variable before running any connector command:

            macOS / Linux:
                  $ export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<your-api-key>

            Windows (Command Prompt):
                  > set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<your-api-key>

            Windows (PowerShell):
                  > $env:ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="<your-api-key>"

OPTIONS
       -h, --help
            Print help information for `bal connector` or a workflow.

EXAMPLES
       Run the full OpenAPI connector pipeline.
           $ bal connector openapi -i ./openapi.yaml -o ./out

       Run the full Java SDK connector pipeline.
           $ bal connector sdk pipeline example-sdk ./out

       Print help for the openapi workflow.
           $ bal connector openapi --help

       Print help for the sdk workflow.
           $ bal connector sdk --help
